	<text>
		<front>
			<p>The series of <hi rend="italic">capitula</hi> published here is unknown to both <ref
					target="#de_Bruyne">de Bruyne</ref> and the <ref target="#Ben">Benedictine
					edition</ref> of the Vulgate. Since it is mainly based on de Bruyne's <ref
					target="https://gallica.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/bpt6k8537228/f125">B series</ref> (as
				observed by P.-M. Bogaert in <ref target="#descrBog">Bogaert et alii</ref>,
				pp. 81-82; see also below), we label it <hi rend="bold">B(a)_dobips</hi>. Among the
				manuscripts recorded in the DOBiPS database, it occurs only in <hi rend="bold"
					>To</hi> (Tournai, Bibliothèque du Séminaire, MS 1), the first volume (the
				second being lost) of the so-called Bible of Lobbes, produced at the eponymous
				Belgian abbey in the late 11th century. <lb/><lb/>As in the case of 2 Regum (here)
				and 4 Regum (here), B(a) combines de Bruyne's <ref
					target="https://gallica.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/bpt6k8537228/f124">A</ref> and <ref
					target="https://gallica.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/bpt6k8537228/f125">B</ref> series,
				while often splitting their <hi rend="italic">capitula</hi> into two or more titles
				and adding further details. <lb/>For example, B's <hi rend="italic">cap.</hi> 2 is
				split into B(a)'s <hi rend="italic">cap.</hi> 3, 4, 5, and 6; the latter three
				develop the final part of B's <hi rend="italic">capitulum</hi> by echoing the
				wording of A's <hi rend="italic">cap.</hi> 3, 4, and 5. The text of the
				above-mentioned chapters is as follows:<list>
					<item>B <list>
							<item>2 <hi rend="italic">De praeceptis dauid quibus instituit salomonem
									et de morte dauid et de interfectione adoniae abiathar ioab et
									semei</hi></item>
						</list></item>
					<item>B(a) <list>
							<item>3 <hi rend="italic">De prȩceptis dauid quibus instituit salomonem
									et de morte dauid</hi></item>
							<item>4 <hi rend="italic">Adonias quem abisach petit in coniugium
									occiditur</hi></item>
							<item>5 <hi rend="italic">Iubente salomone ioab interficitur</hi></item>
							<item>6 <hi rend="italic">Semei occiditur quia non seruauit
									interdictum</hi></item>
						</list></item>
					<item>A <list>
							<item>3 <hi rend="italic">Allegat adonias apud matrem regis salomonis
										<hi rend="underline">petens abisag sunamiten in
										coniugium</hi> unde <lb/>iratus salomon iussit occidi
									fratrem suum adoniam etiam abiathar sacerdotem priuauit honore
									<lb/>parcens sanguini eius</hi></item>
							<item>4 <hi rend="italic"><hi rend="underline">Iubente salomone
										interficitur ioab</hi> ad cornu altaris propter reatum
									occisorum quos ense suo <lb/> iugulauit</hi></item>
							<item>5 <hi rend="italic"><hi rend="underline">Semei occiditur iussu
										regis quia non seruauit concessam sibi semel ueniam</hi> ita
									ne discederet de hierusalem sed contempsit</hi></item>
						</list></item>
				</list>
				<lb/>The point in the text of 3 Regum where To places the chapter number
				corresponding to each <hi rend="italic">capitulum</hi> can be accessed either by
				clicking on the two-page icon next to each <hi rend="italic">capitulum</hi> number,
				or by clicking on the "Passi paralleli" thumbnail (in the right-hand panel of the
				"Testo di lettura" screen).</p>
		</front>
